        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Drainer</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> The main to kill and win a summoning mob:</P><P>Mobs summon after they've had 5% damage done to them.  It used to be only level 51+ mobs summon (true of everything but SoL) but now some green mobs can summon (check out stuff in hollowshade).  Excluding scars of luclin then with the idea that you are actually pulling a mob;</P><P>Pull with a relatively small damaging spell (a level 1 lifetap, or a better choice is splurt -- splurt does little damage to start with and won't put a mob into summoning mode by the time you get back to camp) as mob comes to camp snare it.  Give yourself some space and fear it (level cap of 52 I do believe to fear anything).  Send in the pet, re-snare right away.  Before fear lets off re-fear it.  If fear happens to break at a poor time you will be summoned, don't fret.  Summoning has a reset time (I do believe it to be 12 seconds), run off for a few seconds then cast fear again.  Re-snare right away.  Keep it feared.  Land dots as your confidence builds.</P><P>I used to solo summoners in Skyfire at level 51.  It was good then because if a mob conned even you knew what to expect.  Turns out no one else ever pulled summoners on purpose.</P><P> </font></td>
